{How to continue the attack with white?} 28. g4 $1 ({This shatters Black's
structure from its basement, since his minor pieces are far from the d5-square.
} 28. d5 $2 {is not effective due to} Qg8 29. Qf6+ Kh7 {and Black can defend.})
28... Qg8 ({After a neutral move such as} 28... Bd7 {one possible winning line
is} 29. Qf6+ Qxf6 30. exf6 Kg8 31. g5 Be8 32. d5 $1 {The position is finally
ripe for this.} exd5 33. Bxf5 {and White's far advanced pawns will decide.})
29. Qf6+ Kh7 30. f3 $1 {A very strong "quiet" move defending the g4-pawn and
preparing to unpin it with Kf2.} Bb7 (30... Qg6 {loses the bishop to} 31. Qe7+
Kxh6 32. Qf8+) 31. Kf2 Qg6 32. gxf5 Qxf6 33. exf6 {Threatening f6-f7.} Kxh6 34.
fxe6 Bd5 35. e7 Bf7 36. Bb5 {followed by e7-e8=Q with a won ending.} *

