{The rook is attacked. Where to go? Black to move.} 22... Rd3 $1 {It is
essential to keep the control over the d4-square.} 23. Na5 b6 24. Nb7 {Trying
to prevent ...Nc5.} Bf8 25. Ke2 Rxa3 26. Rhc1 Nc5 27. Bb4 Ra6 $3 {A fatnastic
move creating a X-Ray attack against the e6-pawn.} 28. Nxc5 bxc5 29. Bxc5 Bxc5
30. Rxc5 Rxe6 {with a probable draw.} *

