{[#]} {White's space advantage looks crushing but his structure has an
Chille's heel. Find the best chance for Black} 15... g5 $1 {Immediately
undermining the e5-pawn.} 16. Bh3 e6 $1 ({It is essential to prevent Bxd7+
since after} 16... gxf4 17. Bxd7+ Kxd7 18. Bxf4 {White remains in full control.
}) 17. Rg1 $2 {White cannot resist the temptation to use the offered g-file.} (
17. Qe2 {defeends e5 but allows} gxf4 18. Bxf4 b3+ 19. Kf1 Qxa2 {with two
dangerous queenside passers.}) ({The strongest was} 17. O-O $1 {paradoxically
placing the king on the open file.} gxf4 18. Bxf4 Qa3 19. Bg2 Nxe5 20. Bxe5
Bxe5 21. Qg5 $14 {keeping some light initiative.}) 17... gxf4 18. Rxg7 Nxe5 19.
Ke2 fxe3 $6 ({More precise was} 19... Qa3 $1 20. Bg2 fxe3 21. Qxe3 Qb2+ $1 22.
Kf1 Nd3 $1) 20. Qb2 $2 ({Missing his chance:} 20. Qxe3 Qxa2+ 21. Kf1 {with
unclear play.}) 20... Rxd5 $3 {This leads to a devsatating attack.} 21. cxd5
Qa6+ 22. Kxe3 Qd3+ 23. Kf4 f6 24. Qb3 Ng6+ 25. Rxg6 e5+ 26. Kg4 h5+ 27. Kh4
Qe4+ 0-1

